args.justification: These two relations have the same subject ('ethical dilemmas in AI development') and object ('accountability') and express the same membership semantics as the existing 'includes_ethical_issue' relations (RelR_90a508212138, RelR_9b870085ce73). Normalizing the canonical_rel_name and rel_cls removes an unnecessary predicate variant ('involves_concern') and consistently models all links where the broader ethical dilemmas category includes a specific ethical issue.
args.remark: Consolidated predicate naming for all relations where 'ethical dilemmas in AI development' includes a specific concern, to avoid parallel but redundant predicates ('involves_concern' vs 'includes_ethical_issue').
